        <section id="overview" class="content-section key-advantages fade-in-section"> <div class="container">
                <h2 class="centered-text">What is a Limited Liability Partnership (LLP)?</h2>
                <div class="content-row">
                    <div class="content-text">
                        <h3>Understanding this versatile business structure.</h3>
                        <p>A **Limited Liability Partnership (LLP)** is a popular business structure in India that combines the advantages of both a company and a partnership firm. It offers the benefit of **limited liability** to its partners, protecting their personal assets from the business's debts and liabilities.</p>
                        <p>Unlike traditional partnerships, an LLP is a separate legal entity, giving it perpetual succession and the ability to own assets in its own name. It's governed by the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008, and provides flexibility in internal management, making it an attractive option for professionals, consultants, and service providers looking for a robust yet adaptable business form.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="content-image">
                        <img src="/assets/llp-overview.jpg" alt="Overview of Limited Liability Partnership structure">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="content-section key-advantages fade-in-section"> <div class="container">
                <h2 class="centered-text">Key Features of an LLP</h2>
                <div class="content-row reverse"> <div class="content-image">
                        <img src="/assets/llp-features.jpg" alt="Features of LLP">
                    </div>
                    <div class="content-text">
                        <h3>Why an LLP might be the right choice for you.</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-handshake"></i> **Separate Legal Entity:** The LLP is distinct from its partners.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> **Limited Liability:** Partners are only liable to the extent of their agreed contribution.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-infinity"></i> **Perpetual Succession:** Its existence is independent of its partners.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-users-cog"></i> **Flexible Agreement:** Partnership agreement allows for flexible management structures.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-file-invoice-dollar"></i> **Lower Compliance Burden:** Compared to Private Limited Companies.</li>
                            <li><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> **Easy to Form & Manage:** Relatively simpler registration and operational formalities.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="process fade-in-section"> <div class="container">
                <h2 class="centered-text">Our Streamlined LLP Registration Process</h2>
                <p class="centered-text" style="color: var(--text-light);">Making your LLP incorporation smooth and efficient.</p>
                <div class="process-steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-id-card"></i></div>
                        <h3>1. DIN & DSC Application</h3>
                        <p>Obtain Digital Signature Certificate (DSC) and Designated Partner Identification Number (DPIN) for all designated partners.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i></div>
                        <h3>2. Name Reservation</h3>
                        <p>Apply for reservation of your preferred LLP name with the Ministry of Corporate Affairs (MCA).</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-handshake-alt-slash"></i></div>
                        <h3>3. LLP Agreement Drafting</h3>
                        <p>Prepare the Limited Liability Partnership Agreement, outlining mutual rights and duties of partners.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-file-upload"></i></div>
                        <h3>4. Filing Incorporation Document</h3>
                        <p>Submit Form FiLLiP (Form for Incorporation of Limited Liability Partnership) to the MCA.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-certificate"></i></div>
                        <h3>5. Certificate of Incorporation</h3>
                        <p>Upon approval, receive the Certificate of Incorporation for your LLP.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-icon"><i class="fas fa-university"></i></div>
                        <h3>6. PAN & TAN Allotment</h3>
                        <p>Automatic generation of the LLP's PAN and TAN.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

